;BIOMOLECULE: 1  
THIS ENTRY CONTAINS THE CRYSTALLOGRAPHIC ASYMMETRIC UNIT   
WHICH CONSISTS OF 2 CHAIN(S). SEE REMARK 350 FOR   
INFORMATION ON GENERATING THE BIOLOGICAL MOLECULE(S).   
Helix 1 in chain A is swapped with a symmetry related   
molecule (symmetry operation: (-X, -Y, Z) dx= 1, dy= 1, dz= 0) forming a crystallographic dimer.
;
